<br>
I am on my first real character...I imagine this must have been discussed somewhere and I am just not finding it...  If this has been talked to death, please just post a link to the appropriate message board...  I am mostly interested in how healer types who raid a lot do this...<br>
<br>
How do people set up their screens to minimize spam and maximize their ability to focus on what is important?  And what techniques do you use to go along with that setup?  Just to show what I mean, I will tell you how I do it, even though I am not totally happy with it at the moment...which is why I am posting this question...<br>
<br>
I have three windows set up for chat.<br>
<br>
First window is the main window and has everything I do not stick in the other two...kinda backwards to explain, but just the way it works.  If I see red (out of range, fizzles, etc.),  brown (somebody dies and I may need to clicky them) or yellow (LD messages) text in this window out of the corner of my eye, I look at it.  Fortunately on most raids there is not a lot of spam in these colors, so, this technique works.  If there is a lot of shout spam for example, I move it to window three.<br>
<br>
Second window is what I consider to be the stuff that is most important to constantly monitor in a raid/group.<br>
Tells<br>
Group<br>
Raid<br>
Raid chat channel<br>
Heal channel<br>
My spell effects (buffs dropping, etc.)<br>
<br>
Third window is what I consider to usually be battle spam.  Although I occasionally need to look at it, it is usually not relevant because my primary source of info is watching hp bars (or scanning them in raids if they are other group).  Things like melee/other hits, damage shields, etc. go here.<br>
<br>
In addition to this I have hot keys set up to target MA/SA and main CC person if they are not in my group on a raid.  This allows me to quickly find them if they need heals.<br>
<br>
In my raid window I color code based on their class/role.  <br>
Crowd control roles (chanters, sometimes bards) and sometimes others who are critical to keep alive when it gets really bad and do not tend to have a lot of hps are in white.<br>
<br>
Clerics and any other classes who are healing role are light blue.<br>
<br>
Tanks classes that are most likely to be assigned to get aggro and pick it up if MA/SA die are red (Warrior, Pally, SK, sometimes rangers)<br>
<br>
In addition to keeping my group alive, I tend to watch person I think most likely to die that needs to be kept alive (tends to be puller or MA usually, sometimes a chanter).  If I am not sure, I use hot keys and the colors in raid window to pick people in groups outside mine I think I need to watch most.  Although it depends on situation, if we are getting a lot of adds, it tends to be chanters, MA, healers or anybody I see getting aggro in battle spam window or hear (females make different noise when hit than males, which often helps to figure out who is getting hit when spam flies by.)<br>
<br>
Thanks for any thoughts on this,<br>
Eormid<br>
Cleric of the 59th circle of Rodcet Nife<br>
House of Carnage<br>
