<br>
I tend to put my heal channel in a seperate window, and put my casting messages in that window as well (so I can tell easily when a spell has fizzled).<br>
<br>
I also move my cast bar (the tiny one that shows you casting the spell), and group health window, heal channel window, and my own health window to a bunch somewhere on the screen so they are close to each other and don't require me to look around the screen too much.<br>
<br>
I also pay no attention to the health of the puller. If the puller wants a heal they can ask for it, but healing a puller whilst they are still working on the pull can and most probably will have horrible side effects =)<br>
